Estimated cover of body feathers on the captured bird; percent formatted as a decimal
Body molt score of the captured bird
Trace; Only a very few feathers molting anywhere on the bird’s body in no discernible pattern.
Light; Fewer than one-third of the contour feathers on the bird are molting
Medium; From one to two-thirds of a bird’s contour feathers are in molt.
Heavy; More than two-thirds of the contour feathers on the bird are in molt.
Brood patch score of captured bird
Well defined, breast muscles and gut still visible through the skin
Veined and red; the skin is opaque, thickened or engorged, veined and reed with broad, undulating wrinkles
Wrinkled, the skin has thin wrinkles, engorgement of the skin has gone

Cloacal protuberance score on captured bird
Small; Cloaca somewhat enlarged and noticeably swollen and the shape is conical
Medium; Cloacal protuberance large and the shape is cylindrical
Large; Cloacal protuberance very large and bulbous

Whether downy feathers were collected from the captured bird (Y/N)
No fat in the furculum or anywhere on the body
Trace; A very small amount of fat in the furcular hollow (< 5% filled)
Light; The bottom of the furculum is completely covered but the furcular hollow is less than 1/3 filled
Half; The furcular hollow is about half full, and fat is present under the wingpit and/or on the abdomen
Filled; The furcular hollow is full and a thick layer of fat also occurs under the wing and on the abdomen
Bulging; Fat is bulging slightly above the furculum and well mounded under the wing and on the abdomen
Greatly bulging; Fat is bulging greatly above the furculum and well mounded under the wing and on the abdomen
Very excessive;  fat pads of the furculum, 'wingpit,' and abdomen are bulging so that they join
